BREAKING: Gustavo Gomez' move to Boca Juniors could collapse after Boca wanted to include a certain clause in the player's contract. The player is on his way to Paraguay now. [@cmdotcom]<br />
<br />
@DiMarzio is now also reporting this. He says there is a clause in the player's contract that has infuriated his entourage. The deal is at serious risk.

Mirabelli: &quot;The season starts soon again, and i hope it will be a beautiful one. Transfer market? To the fans, i say not to follow all the names, but we have very clear ideas about arrivals and sales but no one will be sold if Gattuso opposes it. This is a Milan team of Gattuso.&quot;<br />
<br />
Mirabelli: &quot;There was a problem between Gomez and Boca Juniors. Kalinic? He has offers from half of Europe, with Atletico and Sevilla in pole position. Zaza? First, we think about the sales, then we decide if we can afford a sandwich or the meal with caviar and champagne.&quot;
